  "summary": {
    "as": "Reported to House",
    "asOf": "2019-12-18",
    "date": "2020-07-14T13:54:27Z",
    "text": "DHS Countering Unmanned Aircraft Systems Coordinator Act\n\nThis bill directs the Department of Homeland Security (DHS) to designate a DHS official as the Countering Unmanned Aircraft Systems (UAS) Coordinator to coordinate with relevant DHS offices and components, including the Office for Civil Rights and Civil Liberties and the Privacy Office and other relevant federal agencies, on the development of policies and plans to counter threats associated with UAS (i.e., drones).\n\nThe coordinator shall serve as the principal DHS official for disseminating information regarding counter-UAS technology to the private sector."
  },
